<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/23(Sat.) Uber teams with NASA to make flying cars a real &amp;Singapore seen as favorite nation (Host : Ivonne Song )]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=180&amp;p=194#p194"><![CDATA[
Article 1 ~~<br /><br />“Uber teams with NASA to make flying cars a real”<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://money.cnn.com/2018/05/08/technology/uber-nasa/index.html">http://money.cnn.com/2018/05/08/technol ... index.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion ~~<br />1) Before we’re still waiting for our science fiction dreams to come true. But NASA and Uber are bringing the dream closer to reality; do you agree nothing is impossible? <br /><br />2) Are you happy to see flying car Will revolutionize our transportation, or do you have any worry about it?<br /><br />3) Can you imagine we will startup working on flying cars between Taipei and Kaohsiung every day very soon? How do you make rules to help the flying cars safer on the sky if you are a leader of government? <br /><br />4) The flying cars are coming soon. Try to image what will the next step of flying cars?<br /><br />article 2~~<br />Singapore seen as favorite nation: poll - Taipei Times<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/front/archives/2018/06/18/2003695059">http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/front/a ... 2003695059</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion ~<br />1) Do you agree the points of article? What are the value of Singapore? Why?<br /><br />2)Do you have a favorite country or city? Why?<br /><br />3) Do you agree Singapore have a high standard of cleaning and safe?  How can they have such good reputation?<br /><br />4) Do the country achieved remarkable success is related from ruling party or their President? or what else ?<br /><br />Saturday's meeting place:<br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Mon Jun 18, 2018 10:09 pm</p><hr />
